# Build-context hygiene for the login image (Dockerfile.dokploy).
#
# The image only builds the login app (apps/login) + its workspace deps
# (packages/zitadel-client, packages/zitadel-proto) from proto/. But
# `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` must still SEE every workspace package.json
# named in pnpm-workspace.yaml (console, tests/*, apps/*, packages/*,
# deploy/compose) to validate the lockfile. So for the workspaces we do NOT
# build, we keep only their package.json and drop the (heavy) source.

# --- installed / generated artifacts ---
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.open-next
**/.turbo
**/dist
**/coverage
**/*.log
.git

# --- generated proto output (rebuilt in-image) ---
packages/zitadel-proto/zitadel
packages/zitadel-proto/google
packages/zitadel-proto/validate
packages/zitadel-proto/protoc-gen-openapiv2
packages/zitadel-client/dist

# --- Go backend & non-JS tooling (not part of the login build) ---
internal
cmd
pkg
backend
statik
openapi
main.go
go.mod
go.sum
buf.work.yaml
.golangci.yaml
.github
.devcontainer

# --- workspace packages we don't build: keep only package.json ---
console/*
!console/package.json
apps/docs/*
!apps/docs/package.json
tests/*
!tests/functional-ui
tests/functional-ui/*
!tests/functional-ui/package.json
deploy/*
!deploy/compose
deploy/compose/*
!deploy/compose/package.json
benchmark

# --- env files (never bake developer env into the image) ---
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.theme.example
